<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">Distribution</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">
New records: Western Predbalkan, Banitsa vill., 21.08-28.08.1994, Malaise traps, 3 m., leg. T. Ljubomirov. Detailed occurrence data: 
<bibRefCitation author="Lapeva-Gjonova, A." journalOrPublisher="Biodiversity Data Journal" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" refId="B7741022" refString="Lapeva-Gjonova, A., Borowiec, L., 2022. New and little-known ant species (Hymenoptera, Formicidae) from Bulgaria. In: Biodiversity Data Journal. Occurrence dataset." title="New and little-known ant species (Hymenoptera, Formicidae) from Bulgaria" volumeTitle="Biodiversity Data Journal. Occurrence dataset." year="2022">Lapeva-Gjonova and Borowiec (2022)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">Notes</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">
Despite the rare finding of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Emery" baseAuthorityYear="1869" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Strumigenys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Strumigenys argiola" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="argiola">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">Strumigenys argiola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, it is widespread in Europe and North Africa. This species was reported very recently for the first time from one locality in Bulgaria (Northeast Bulgaria, SW from Balchik) (
<bibRefCitation author="Lapeva-Gjonova, A." journalOrPublisher="Sociobiology" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" pagination="326 - 329" refId="B7725858" refString="Lapeva-Gjonova, A., Ljubomirov, T., 2020. First records of two Strumigenys ant species (Hymenoptera, Formicidae) from Bulgaria. Sociobiology 67 (2): 326 - 329" title="First records of two Strumigenys ant species (Hymenoptera, Formicidae) from Bulgaria" volume="67" year="2020">Lapeva-Gjonova and Ljubomirov 2020</bibRefCitation>
). The presented record supplements the knowledge on its distribution in Bulgaria.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
